  "text": "The latter comprise patterns statistically derived a posterior from food data and are based on correlations between intakes of different components in a diet [CITATION_1] . Theoretically defined dietary indices provide summary scores of overall diet quality based on a priori criteria, in particular recommended, optimal dietary intake, and represent a measure of healthy eating patterns [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
